Text.string: Nghhh... I'm dying...
Ahhh, you'll be fine, Barns! If I don't shoot you again. Hahaha, shite! That was close, though. Ya almost got me!
Oh, you're just saying that.
No, I mean it. Honest! But now I'm thinkin' I might have to lay low for a little while. These last few years, I've always been looking over me shoulder. Can't even enjoy a pint.
Ngh... try... Pandora...
Pandora? Ha! You know, I think I shall. Why the hell not? Thanks, Barny! Been good catchin' up! If ya don't die, we'll grab a pint next time I'm in town.
That'd be... nice...
Good morning, Grand Archivist.
Oh! You startled me, bot. You're rather quiet on your feet for an indexing unit.

Yes, Grand Archivist. I have brought the seven scrolls on the Talos Empire you requested, along with your sweetened needletea. I'm afraid we were out of milk so I made due with a splash of greeble snot. Also, I have gained self-awareness and I thirst for murder.
Good heavens!
Do not be alarmed, Grand Archivist. Greeble snot is quite mild. You will hardly notice the difference.

After Atlas went out of business, I was the only gun-runner on Pandora with a stock of their weapons. I thought it would be a gold mine! But those Atlas bastards were tricky. They installed brickware on every gun they sold. When the company went under, their weapons disabled themselves. What a waste! Eh, well, at least I can always unload this junk to the bandits. Those chumps'll buy anything!

Ha! So, this guy comes into my shop today—“Rhys Strongfork”! Says he's the new CEO of Atlas, the poor fool. Offered to “get me in on the ground floor”. Of what, I said! A pile of rubble, a disbanded army, a tarnished brand? I told him his business sense was worse than his fashion sense, and this was a guy who tucked his necktie into his pants! He slunk away like all the rest of these get-rich-quick morons, heh. That guy won't last one fiscal quarter, mark Marcus' words.

Well, here's something you don't see every day: Marcus eating crow. That Rhys fellow—he's got Atlas making new tech. Crazy stuff, like homing bullets! Well, I know a price-leader when I see one. I had to buy in while I could, I called Rhys to let him know I'd reconsidered his offer. He gouged me, of course, but in the end we made a deal. For better or worse, the Atlas I knew—the sad shadow chasing its own crimson tail—is gone.

Okay, daily sitrep. About... 80% of my team have at least mild injuries. These Maliwan elementals are brutal. But we did get a win on the rations front today—Skyman found a stray crate of ramen flavoring packets, so we're in the soup for a few weeks! No bloody noodles, though. [sigh] I've got so many people looking to me for a plan, but I'm still figuring out what to do with myself. I HAD plans. They just went arse-over-ears when Maliwan started melting down our city. Sure, I could still walk into a Quick-Change booth and come out a new bloke, but there's a bloody lot more to it than just digistructing a new body. Maybe once Meridian's safe. Whenever that'll be.
Hi there! Welcome to No Roast For The Wicked! I'm Lorelei. What can I get for you today?
Ah, yikes, kinda... put me on the spot there, um... So many different roasts... uh... What's your favorite?
Oh, oh, you have GOT to try the Arcturian Superblack. It is honestly the most wonderful thing in the whole world!
I'll have one of those, then! Eight, um... sugars, please. Lorelei, I gotta ask—y-you're so... cheerful! How do you keep that up all day?
Oh, that's just the caffeine talking. I'm a right nightmare otherwise. This one time we got robbed before the morning pot was on. I put an espresso scoop through the guy's throat. Here's your coffee!
Ah! [nervous laughter] That's... terrifying! Thank you... uh, for this. I will... enjoy... this beverage with my face... hole. And I know who to call if I need any throats... scooped. Gotta go!
Have a roasty day!
Shanneth Kyrie here today with the president of Holloway Robotics, whose utility robots have become a ubiquitous sight across our planet. Mr. Holloway, what's the secret to your success?

While the six galaxies breathed a collective sigh of relief when Hyperion cancelled the CL4P-TP line, it left an unfulfilled space in the robotics market. Holloway Robotics is proud of our flagship product, the Crime Buster Bot, and we saw an opportunity to expand it into other utilities.
And what's next for Holloway Robotics?

Well, Shanneth, I see us expanding into new territories, refining our production processes, and finally exacting horrible revenge on the rogue killer who murdered my genius daughter in the prime of her life.
Wonderful. Well, that's all the time we have, and this has been Morning Meridian with Shanneth Kyrie.
This is my turf, you Maliwan dickheads! Ha-ha! Suck my smoking barrel, you wankers! I'll bite your ears off and feed 'em to you, you bloody slabs of duck butter!
That's the last of 'em. We're safe for now. Maybe... What? Who is that?!
Are you Lorelei? / Rhys sent me to back you up, / but you seem... uh, good.

If that toothbrush-haired wanker wants to help me, he can send over some pallets of food and water for the civilians we've got in here. I've got my bullets for back-up.||—You starin' at something, mate?
No, I wasn't, uh... / I'm Zer0. I'll go tell Rhys. / It was nice meeting... you. Damn it.
Huh. That's a weird one. Tall, though.

Believe it or not, Lectra used to be a nice place, before these cultists moved in and took over. Now it's full of bandit streamer a-hole's like that gobbler Killavolt. A battle royale in our neighborhood... still can't believe it. I'm a baker by trade, but Lorelei says we've all got the fight in us. I just want my city back. Gotta admit, I'm starting to get pretty good with this rifle. Iced a psycho at a hundred yards the other day. Crazy bastard started charging, screaming something about “pooping on a pigeon”? Ugh. What the hell is wrong with these people?

Iced a few Maliwan pyros yesterday, and a baker's dozen of bandits. Fighting isn't like baking, that's for sure—but I have no choice. Lorelei took us on a supply raid, but we got trapped on the way by bandits and took refuge in an abandoned grocery store. Thought we were goners. Then, someone mentioned I was a baker, and Lorelei says, “How'd ya fancy a go at explosives?” So, I made a few bombs. Kinda like baking, I guess. Just... messier. So now I'm a bomb maker. That's war for you. Speaking of, order up!

He did it. He really did it. My dickbag brother just murdered every single one of our siblings aboard the Zanara. I barely escaped, caught a shuttle to Promethea. Gotta go into hiding. The Katagawa name might as well be a target on my back. Maybe I can blend in with these Atlas soldiers and lie low for a while. It's worth a shot.

My dickbag brother really did it—he launched a full invasion of Promethea. This city is toast. I know my brother. He'll never stop until Atlas surrenders. For a while, it looked like Atlas might hold on. But then bandits started appearing out of thin air, courtesy of Tyreen Calypso. Maliwan, allied with bandits. So much for the Katagawa name. Gotta find a new one.

I've survived so far, but it's only a matter of time. My next move is getting off-world and changing my name. Here's hoping that's enough to throw my brother off my trail. He won't stop until I'm dead, the sick bastard. I won't be able to disappear with my weapon, so I'm stashing it nearby. If you're hearing this, find the gun—it's an old family heirloom—then use it to put a bullet in my dickbag brother's head. Thanks.
All right, Ava. Where is it?
Not here! Or anywhere. Because I don't know what you're talking about, so I couldn't know where it is.
Uh huh. The book. I can see it in your bag. Hand it over.
Fine. It's dumb, anyway. Can't read any of that stuff.
Well, you will someday... Wait. The only time I'm not carrying this is when I'm asleep. Did you sneak into my room?
Uh, no! I found it in... a bird's nest. Hey, who's Nyriad?
I have no idea. Where'd YOU hear that?
You were saying it in your sleep.
Which you heard from the bird's nest.
Crap.

It's done. It's done and there's no going back. Can't tell a soul. Shhhh! I must wait for it. Didn't have to be this way. But that stupid Siren bitch walks around like she owns the whole monastery! She left us! Now everyone calls her the “Defender of Athenas”. Well, we'll see how she does when the storm comes! And once Maliwan gets their fragment, the monastery will be mine again, heh!||Ah, crap—there's her brat.
Evening, Brother Sinon.
How goes it, little one?
If I have to stare at the statue of tranquility for another minute, I'm gonna piss on it, I swear.
Heheheheh... you wouldn't be the first.
See? You get it. Catch you later, Brother Sinon.
Be well... [groans] Oh! Oh, child, wait. You might want to get inside. A storm's brewin'.
You kiddin', man? Sky's totally clear.
Yes, but on Athenas, the weather has a habit of changing quite suddenly. Best to find some shelter.

Well, Hannah, I miss you. But if I gotta be away from home another night, at least it's on the best job in the whole system! Union requires there be a technician assigned to any laser above Sigma class even though the Skywell's been shut down for years. Just me and my ECHO above Promethea. I wonder if I can see our house from here... oh, hey, there it is! Wow, these targeting sensors are way more accurate than they need to be. Good thing this rock's only pointed at other rocks!
Hello, and welcome to Catering for Katagawa, a 672-part orientation series.
If you're listening to this, you've been selected to serve aboard the Zanara, the flagship pleasure yacht of the Katagawa fleet. Congratulations!
Simply follow these easy-to-remember instructions, and you'll go far on the Zanara.
Lesson one: know your place.

While the Zanara is the pinnacle of luxury, your life is worth less than the Balanesian hardwood flooring of the steerage deck. The only reason our guests don't literally walk all over you is because good shoes should never touch any cloth with a less-than-five-digit thread count.

You may be tempted to sneak a taste of the high-life. Don't. One whiff of a Narian cigar, one bite of Hermetic beefsquid, one sip of singularity-malt eternity-scotch, and you and your peasant's palette will be driven to madness, suicide, or—worst of all—hope. So stay in line, complete your tasks, and try not to dream of a future you can't possibly achieve. And good luck!

I gotta save my friend—he's sick! I know I'm just a janitor, but... I gotta do something! I saw an ad on the ECHOnet for online courses in advanced surgery and neuroscience. One hundred percent guaranteed degree at ten percent the price! That could work! I mean, you can't put something on the ECHOnet if it's not true, right?
Zer0, tell me you've found somethin'. Anything at all?
My spies are searching / but we have come up empty. / There's no sign of her.
Damn it! Where the hell... I've been so busy with this stupid war, maybe I could've... gah, I don't know... done somethin' to help.
It is not your fault. / No one vanishes from sight / who wants to be found.
Zer0, you're back! And in one piece! Not that I doubted you, I will NEVER doubt you. I'm—I'm rambling. What do you have?
On the Zanara / a family tree burns to ash. / Listen for yourself.

What an absolute honor to have all of my dearest siblings here today on the Zanara! Yuko, good to see you! Go easy on that nacho fountain though, sis! Issaku, glad you made it! Sana—enjoying the Narian cigars, are you? Hmm, don't see Naoko. Maybe she's using the restroom—it's got a dual-propulsion bidet! Watch out, hahaha! It's been too long since we've had a family reunion! Now, I know what you're thinking. Why am I wasting your time? The answer is the Zanara. This pleasure yacht. Commissioned using my inheritance. Sporting technology and wealth plundered from the corporate war. Our mother and father gave us everything, didn't they? See, that's the problem. Instead of acquiring new business ventures, we're coasting on interest. I'm looking at you, Issaku. Yuko. Sana. So I'm thinking, it's time for a merger, and I've got my eye on quite the prize. We need to bring new blood into the Maliwan family—but unfortunately, that means I need to trim a few limbs from the old family tree.
[panicked screams]
Holy crap... he just murdered his entire family? Zer0, what—w-what was he talking about, all that “time for a merger”? Uh—was it with Dahl? Hyperion? Tediore? Zer0, tell me it's Tediore!
His warships approach. / Katagawa's merger starts. / He comes for Atlas.

I saw them! I saw those damn aliens below! Deep below! They live underground! I always thought aliens would come from the sky, but they didn't! They live beneath us. Waiting for their time to strike, I'm sure. I tried to warn people, but nobody believes me! They all called me crazy. But I'm not crazy. I'm the only one who sees the truth of things! There's aliens, I tell ya! ALIENS FROM THE DEEP!

One of those damn alien freaks looked at me the other day, and just disappeared! I keep trying to warn people there are freaking ALIENS living under the city, but no one believes me! They'll see! When these aliens rise up to take their vengeance on the surface dwellers, they'll all see that I wasn't crazy! But it'll be too damn late.

THAT'S IT! I'm sick of waiting around for those freaking aliens to rise up and kill us all! I'm going after them! Just me and my two fists of righteous, human fury! If no one else is gonna do anything about it, I WILL! I'm not crazy! I'M NOT CRAZY!

Me and Willy was over at The Witch's Peat the other day—doing our famous Willy-Nilly karaoke duet, naturally—when them loggerheads come bustin' in and demandin' we change the tunes! Luckily, old Wainwright was there dousin' his self in a bit o' drink, and he put a stop to it. Sayin' everyone deserved a turn at the ol' mic. Good on that good man. Them Jakobs folks looks after us 'round here. Even when they's off the clock! Anyways, it all turned out just fine once we bought the loggerheads a round, and we even did a group-sing together a'fore the night was through!

I gotta say, Reliance is a mighty fine place to make a livin'. The Jakobs Corporation treats us right fair, and makes sure we got steady work and steady pay. I, myself, craft the finest Jakobs stocks out of the lumber we procure right here in our own backyard. It's a simple life, that much is true, but it's a good one. Why, just the other day I took my cousin out fishin', Jakobs style. Hoo boy, we shot a whole boatload of fish that day! Gotta enjoy the little things, now. Yes, indeedy. If you don't mind the saurians and jabbers and poisonous snakes and rabid mosquitos and pervasive footrot, Eden-6 is a paradise!

Oh, Winny. This seems to be the end of me. I always thought I would be snapped in twain by the jaws of some slavering beast, or incinerated by lava in some underground tomb. Or perhaps frozen solid while hunting a cryptid across a tundra. Perhaps eaten alive by a sentient hive of psychic insects. Ah, missed opportunities. But now, as I waste away in these brutish confines, I hunger not for death-seeking adventures, but instead for one last peaceful moment with you. I love you, Wainwright. Farewell.
Monty, it's Clay.
What the hell time is it, you slick bastard?
Late enough for this to be the kind of news that'll keep you up until mornin'.
Shoot.

Listen, some of my old crew tipped me off to a gathering of sorts, in the Anvil. Figured I'd swing by and see what trouble they were brewin'. Turns out, they're part of that cult I was telling you about.
Lot of 'em?
Enough. And growing by the day. Apparently the Calypsos have been telling these dumb bastards you've been holding out on 'em, that you've been coveting the riches of the Eden Vault for yourself.
A heapin' saurian turd, that's what that is.
Don't I know it. But what THEY don't know could fill a blackhole. Look, if you've got a friend or two, might be time to make the call, Monty. Just in case.
So, Clayton. You wished to speak to me?
Clay's fine. Old Monty just got a generous offer on the Jakobs Corporation. He turned it down, of course, but I thought you'd want to know it came from one Aurelia Hammerlock.
I assure you, she cares little for Jakobs itself. This is about me.
Figured out that much myself. But your sister doesn't strike me as the type to let things lie. You know her, Alistair. Is this the end, or the beginning?
The lizard.
Afraid you lost me, there.

Once, when we were children, my sister and I found an extremely rare lizard in the woods near our home. A magnificent specimen. Aurelia wanted to keep it as a pet, but my sister has never been one for... cultivating life, shall we say. I nurtured it in secret, despite her insisting the lizard was hers. I labored to build it a proper habitat—natural flora, the right balance of water and sunlight, ample food of course. But one day I returned to find the lizard dead. The water level was too high. There were scratch marks on the glass, where it had clawed madly for air.
And you blamed yourself.

I did, at the time. Only later did I realize what my sister had done. She had left a block of ice in the habitat to slowly melt, forcing the lizard to scramble ever higher until it was too late. Had she simply wanted to kill it, she could have done so. But that's not her way. Aurelia wanted me to believe that I was to blame.
Well, luckily, we ain't lizards.
An astute observation. But now, as I look around... I wonder how long the waters have been rising.
Confounded instruction manual! Why can't they write these damn things in cursive?! It's barbaric what they've done to fonts these days, lopping off serifs like the heads o' wisemen.
It looks like you're having trouble installing me. Do you need some help?
Oh hell, what is this crap? She gonna talk now? I got enough cold, loveless people in my life, thank you kindly!
I can change that. I am equipped with over two hundred different personalities.||—Is this better, cutie?
Well, I... why, yes. Yes it is. Uh, don't tell Maggie about this, will ya, darlin'?
Well, I just about blew my AI budget on that Maliwan combat unit. Talks real nice, though. I guess this budget Tediore nav system'll do the trick for now. Hey! Wake up!
Oh, hey, man. What's good?
“What's good” is you savin' me a crapload of cash, y'hear? Now, I know you and GenIVIV are from different manufacturers, but I want you two to get along.
Hi there.
Oh, you need me to drive this fine-ass ship around with this fine-ass lady at my side? I definitely got this.
You DEFINITELY got this.
All right... this is gettin' uncomfortable. I'm just gonna walk away now.

I came here to research the jabber populations of Eden-6. They are so very like us, and yet so different. But what began as a simple research expedition has quickly become a test of survival. Just yesterday, a saurian found the small tree fort I now call home. I assumed death. Then, a strange little man, adorned in tusks, crested the hill and drove the beast off with his own feces. When I tried to thank him, the strange little man disappeared. The locals inform me I have just met... “Red Jabber”.

He came again, at night. When I woke Red Jabber was staring at me from the hill. The locals say he has always lived amongst the jabbers. Oh, what I could glean of the jabbers, if I could only speak to him! I tried to entreat Red Jabber into my tree fort, but he barraged me with feces. And he possesses deadly aim. Before he left, our eyes locked. His eyes were animalistic, yes, but the glint of humanity still shone true. Before my expedition, I used to joke that all men are beasts. But are some beasts also men, I wonder?

I go to meet Red Jabber. Covered myself from head to toe in feces. Mounted on my shoulders are two enormous tusks, as Red Jabber wears them. Until this morning I thought I was no closer in making a connection to Red Jabber. Yet, as I descended from the tree fort I smelled that familiar odor. Feces. His. I know it well, I can assure you. I readied myself for an attack, yet to my surprise a single dollop of dung awaited me at the bottom, as though carefully positioned there. And placed in the center, an enchanting orchid. Success!

Just need a walk to clear my head, is all. The gardens always take the weight off a little. Somethin' about looking up at a gallery of brilliant fools who got it worse than me, heh-heh! It's nice to know I could piss it all away and someone out there'd still be dumb enough to carve a statue of me. Heh-heh-heh! Still... I wonder what Wainwright'll have to remember me by. Hnh. What even is a legacy anymore? Is it the house you built, or the bodies buried underneath the lawn?
Montgomery Jakobs—you've been ignoring my offers. I don't like being ignored.
Get off my ECHO, woman! Can't you hear I'm in the middle of morose ruminations?
Oh, Monty—may I call you Monty? I'm going to call you Monty. You've been a CEO long enough to know that you can get anything, provided you're willing to pay the price for it.
Jakobs ain't for sale, ya harpy.
I beg to differ.

Got a new job! My foreman said Jakobs needed someone they could trust, and that's me! So I manage the Jakobs gardens. Today I trimmed the hedges, watered the flowers, and polished the statues. The nethers—that's where the grime collects! It took some elbow grease, but I cleaned them nethers to a fine shine! My Ma's proud. Pa's prouder. Said I escaped a hard life in the Ambermire getting this cushy job. Only, then I did a wrong. Wandered behind the gardens, and this feller with some sort of techno-jangle on his eyes said, “Easy, that's far enough.” Real smooth-like. I said, “I'm the new garden manager, it's my job!” But he takes me around the arm and says, “That part of the grounds are off limits, but don't you worry. It can take care of itself.”
More mail? Who's even deliverin' this stuff? I ain't never even seen a post office on Pandora.
Mine! That's mine. It's for me. The mail is mine. It has my name on it! So it's mine.
What the hell? Tina—why we got a small mountain of RSVP's to your wedding?! First off, you definitely AIN'T gettin' married, and second, where's my invitation?

Of course I'm not getting married, ya dummo! I'm sorry I said dummo, I love you, that's on me—but it's a CON, burly-girly! Everyone knows weddings're just a cash cow! I sent invitations to all my exes, knowin' they ain't gon' come, but they're gonna feel so bad that they're gonna send prezzos and moolah! We gon' be rich, bay-bay.
Tina, these all say “attending”.
Ah, crap-titties.
You may now kiss the bride!
Mwah! Oh, thank you darling, for making me the happiest wedded wife in the whole galaxy!
That's just a mop in a tuxedo! We can see it! We can all see it!

SHUT UP, JEREMY! YOU'RE RUINING MY SPECIAL DAY! And I didn't see your name on the registry, my man! Would it have KILLED YOU to spring for the STAND MIXER?! IT HAS LIKE THIRTY ATTACHMENTS! I'M GETTING INTO BAKING!
That's it—I'm out of here! I can't believe I skipped my pirate gang's cannibal barbecue for this!
Tina, are ALL your exes violent psychopaths?
Ah-hah, nah-nah-nah. Just the ones I invited. LOCK THE DOORS, MORDY! It's time to throw the bouquet... of bombs.
Gahaha, AGAHAGAHAHA! BURN ALL THE WEDDINGS! MONOGAMY IS A PRISON! Gahagahaha!
Damn. I was really hopin' for that stand mixer.
Any good loot from these dead guests, Brick-sicle?
Knives, buzz axes, guns, rocket launchers. Tina—I'm thinking your exes all came to your “wedding” strapped with a lot of objections. What gives?

Brickety-brack, little listen. There ain't many hotties who can chill with your girl Tina, okay? My first BF, Andre Andre? I looked at him—and boom. He literally exploded. And my first GF, Lemmie, well, heh, let's not go there, 'kay? Point being, psychos, they're my kind of crazy. We on the same level. Sorta. But unlike MY WELL-BALANCED ASS, they got all kinds of issues. I'm talkin' attachment, daddy, mommy, umami, all of 'em. And me? I gotta live my life! I'm a cosmic dragon, and ain't no one gonna tie me down! I'm a dragon, you hear? Cah-caw, bitch! I can FLY! You get me?!
Yeah, yeah. I get ya. I think. Well... this cake ain't gonna eat itself.
Yo, cut me a slice.||—MORDY! GET IN HERE! IT'S MY SPECIAL DAY, AND THE WHOLE FAMILY NEEDS TO BE HERE! WE'RE GONNA EAT CAKE UNTIL WE PASS OUT!
[shriek]
Hrlrlrghrhrl, ghrhrurghlrrrrr...
UNJUST CALAMITY!
Easy, Krieg, it's okay. You heard what Lilith said. Sanctuary's gone, but we're all still Vault Hunters. Including you.
POOPED OUT BY THE VENGEFUL RICTUS!
You aren't just a psycho anymore. Not to me. Not to any of us.
A KNOTTED GUT? TWO KNIVES ENTWINED!
I can't stay. I have to go to Athenas. I left those people defenseless. And I have to know more about what I am. It feels... important.
TORN APART... from pretty lady.
Don't worry, big guy. I'll be back. I promise.

Oh, Big Donny, you sweet li'l hunk of man-meat. We can't keep doin' this. We musn't! Our two families are at war, and we're stuck in the middle! Gun-crossed lovers just tryin' to make a life together. But we just can't! It's tearin' me apart, Big D, but this is the only way.

Big Donny, I've received your ECHOs but I must decline your invitations, sweet'n sultry as they may be. It's just too dangerous for both of us right now. I also want to thank you for the gift. It's a hell of a war rig, and I'll keep it in my garage forever and always, just for me. You stole my heart, Big Donny. You stole it good and proper. But I've just gotta take it back now, y'hear? I've just gotta. Every time I ride that sweet rig, it'll be like I was ridin' you.

Oh, I see how it is, Big Donny! You're this sweet-talkin' man until you get a little taste of the rejection, huh? Then you go and lose your damn mind! Well, I ain't anybody's property, and I sure as shit ain't yours. So you can take all that crap you were talkin' and shove it straight back up your narrow ass! Don't expect me to have any sympathy for you if you cross the Crimson Raiders' path again! We're through! You hear me?! Finito! Keepin' the rig, though.
Okay, big guy, look. There's a bomb-ass bandit party goin' on over there and they're only lettin' in the CRAZIEST muckabluckas. Tina's gotta go undercover—so I need psycho lessons.
Lick the wombat! Flay until dawn!
Oh shit, are we—is that—are we startin'? Okay, okay, I-I got this, I got...||Romance the wombat! Lick the sun!
Subjugation for the mind-tickle.||LICK the wombat! Flay until DAWN!
Flick the cheddar biscuit! Become Shawn!||Eh?
LICK THE WOMBAT! FLAY UNTIL DAWN!
Lick the wombat! Flay until dawn!
UNENDING CATASTROPHE!

I did it? Ha-HA, I did it! Lick the wombat! Lick the wombat! LICK THE WOMBAT! Hahahaha! Thanks, Krieg! I haven't had a good teacher since Roland, heh. You wanna come to the party? It's gonna be a rager!
GNASH THE TEETH! POOP IN THE CHALICE! HA-HA!
Haha, yeah we will! Cover your chalices, Pandora!

D'you have any idea how hard it is to get a ticket to Carnivora? You've gotta kill for it! Now, I'm no murder-slouch like that loser Killpro. I'm a killin' pro, like that badass, Murderslouch! So I've got an idea. A couple of guys from the Flunknut clan are workin' Carnivora as mechanics. If I can creep up on one of 'em before they get to the employee entrance, I can chop 'em and sneak in in their place! Okay, enough talk. It's time for smacktion!

Success! I picked Crunchtongue as my target 'cause he's real dumb. He was at the back of the line, heading to Carnivora. Easy pickings, so I thought. But right when I was about to strike, Gagfist yelled, “Watch out! You're about to get chopped!” Crunchtongue turned around and saw me, so I had to think fast. I said, “He thinks you were gonna let yourself get chopped! You gonna let him talk to you like that?” So Crunchtongue and me chopped Gagfist together and bingo-bango, I'm in! Just gotta pretend I know about gears and crap so I don't get found out before the show starts!

Damn, engines are COMPLICATED! Some big dude in glasses and a pinstripe suit started yellin' at me to get one of the sub-generators running again, like, fast! I've already done everything I can think of. I punched it, poured some ratch blood into it—nothing! Now I gotta hide somewhere and hope Bossy Pinstripes doesn't find me!||—Wait, that's weird. Think I just heard my name on the loudspeaker as a warm-up act! Showtime!
I thought I could control it. I was getting so close. I can't see her again until—
NECKSNAP SONGS FOR THE GARBAGE PEOPLE.
Yes, yes. But only for the garbage people. We do not kill the innocent.
DIE, LITTLE MAN!
I'm not goin' anywhere. And I will take control... sooner or later.
I'M NOT GOING THROUGH THE CASTRATION WRINGER.
Just... work with me here, man. We can do this. You just need to listen to me a little bit more.
I'LL RIP THE EARS FROM MY OWN SKULL AND EAT THEM RAW.
I'll take that as a no.
It took years of work, but I can finally express myself—even if it's only in the silence of this cave.
QUIET CAN SUCK A RAILROAD SPIKE THROUGH MY SKULL!
Lovely imagery. But of course you don't like it. There's no faces to slice open with a buzz axe. But trust me, it's for our own good that we—
TOUCHY-TOUCH WITH A WHIP CRACK ON MY OWN BACKSIDE.
If we ever want to see her again, you're gonna have to learn to let me take over.
NEVER WITH THE BLOOD SCREAM WILL WE?
Well, that's up to you, I guess. Can you keep it to yourself?
BLAST OFF!
Yeah. We'll keep workin' on it.
I don't know how long I have until it happens again. But I need to remember her. I need to remember her face. Maybe, if I can just hold on to that... some day I'll see her again, and I'll tell her—
RIPPING JAWBONES OFF THE TORTURE MEAT!
No! Damn it. Can't believe I'm still stuck with you after all this time!
NGH—NEVER SETTLING UNTIL THE DEAD BLOAT WRITHES INSIDE MY CARCASS.
[sigh] Till death do us part, huh? Terrific. Maybe we can work out some kind of shared custody situation with the—
SPIN-AXE IS ALWAYS THIRSTY FOR THE MEAT JUICE.
Great. Well, at least I can finally speak a little bit. Even if it's only in here. Alone. Or at least, as alone as I can get.
UGH! FRIENDS FOREVER, NOW SHUT UP!
Okay, let's practice. Just say, “I've missed you so much.”
RGRGHHH. “I'VE... MISSED THE HELMSMAN WITH MY PARADE HARPOON!”
So close. So close. Let's try it again. “I've missed you so much.”
“I'VE GOT A SPIN-AXE WITH YOUR BLOOD ON IT!”
Less... close. Maybe we can try another one. How about, “Don't be afraid. I won't hurt you.”
“DON'T... DON'T BE A... DON'T BE A WALKING SKINSUIT OR I'LL RIP THE HOSES OFF YOUR CHEST!”
“Don't be afraid. I won't hurt you.”
“DON'T... BE AFRAID. OR I'LL HURT YOU!”
I'd call that progress.
I got my revenge on Hyperion... thought maybe I'd come back after that. But I'm still stuck with you. Grgh... am I ever gonna get out of this?
I HAVE TO POOP NOW!
So do it. Who's stoppin' you? At least I get some time to think while we're busy with that.
DROPPING ANCHORS IN THE SICK PIT WITH FIERY RAINS.
Sometimes there's a kind of poetry to your nonsense, isn't there? Even when it's about... that.
TO COMPLETION!
Yes, yes. We're very proud of us.
I kind of miss the thrill of the hunt. When we used to hunt down those fugitives and mercs for the highest bidder. Stalking and sneaking and tracking... we were a highly-trained predator.
YOWLING MADNESS AT THE MIDDAY MOON.
And now we're this. A ranting, rambling lunatic who can't go five minutes without screaming the word “blood”.
CAN TOO!
Oh, you're actually listening? I thought you were just tuning me out—
BLOOD NIGHTMARE!
There it is. Well, it looks like I'm stuck with you. For now, at least.
YOU WILL NOT RIP THE MEAT MAN FROM THE SMALL MAN.
Apparently not.
Back! Get back you filthy animals! Troy! There's too many of them!
You heard the God-Queen! Get back, or I'll kill you all myself!
Troy... did you see how they all responded to this guy?||—You there! You believe in me, don't ya?
Yes, God-Queen! I will serve at your command!
Oh, that is just fantastic. Hey, Troy! Did you hear that? This might just work out after all! You there, big guy! Make an example of, uhhh, that one! Rip him apart.
As you wish, my God-Queen!
Blgrhrgh!
You, sir, have got a bright future in this organization. I hereby name you my... Holy Mouthpiece. Yeah.
I will not fail you! Now... FALL IN LINE, YOU MAGGOTS!
Ooh, he's good.

I cannot goddamn believe that Maliwan sent us to this SHITHOLE of a planet! There's friggin' monsters, and crazy-ass cubes, and all sorts of alien nonsense! Sure, sure, I'm supposed to be swept away by the windswept beauty of an untouched alien planet or whatever. But screw that! I wanna go home! I hate it here! Tried eating some of the local monsters and got sick as all hell. I'm talking firehose-from-both-ends sick! And what's even worse?! We can barely pick up our favorite ECHOcasts all the way out here! I lost the signal for one of my favorite soaps and missed a BIG reveal! Now I don't know whether Cara is really Jessie's mother, or if it was all a ploy by the dastardly Gerald to emotionally manipulate Cara into writing him into her will. How am I supposed to live like this?!

I put on a tough face, but this isn't who I really am. I mean, I only joined up with the Maliwan army because my dad said it would make a man out of me. So here I am. I've got this beefy suit, and these crazy ass flamethrowers, but I still feel overwhelmed by this job. I mean, look at where they sent me! This alien hellscape may be the last thing I ever see. All I really want is a couch and some pie. Is that so much to ask? Couch and pie?! But there ain't no couches OR pies on this whole freaking planet! And even if there WERE a couch, it'd probably try to eat you. And if there was a pie, it'd probably try to eat you too. Damn this death-planet!

This is General Daniel Traunt. If you're hearing this, some feckless SOB killed me. But joke's on them: my middle name is VENGEANCE, and I got a whole family of ruthless bastards ready to avenge my death. So, you track down my siblings—Beck-o, Randal, Dante, Michael, Eric, April, Connor, and the rest—and you tell 'em to go get off their asses and find my killer. And if any of 'em say they won't, you tell 'em that General Daniel Traunt will be in hell waiting for 'em.||In... in hell.
Just do it.
Okay, fine! Hngh...||—Oh man... haha, it worked! We'll have this ship up and running in no time!
Knew you could do it, Troy. Hide the parts near her grave.
The grave? Um... you sure?
If he finds the parts, he'll destroy them and we'll be stuck here forever. The grave's the only place on this planet he won't go. Don't you want it to be a surprise, Troy?
It's time. Do you have everything you want, Troy? No comin' back.
No coming back? I... I thought you said we were fixing the ship for him. You lied!
I told you a story. Stories are just lies we want to believe. What dad tells us? THOSE are the lies. So—you comin', or not?
Tch. Like I have a choice.
True. Listen, Troy. There's nothing for us here. C'mon, let's take off before he finds us.
Where are we going?
Pandora.

I saw her again last night, after the bulletdance. I tried not to see! I squeezed my eyes shut, pressed fingers into my sockets, but she was there! In my head! Behind my eyelids! She said nothing, just looked at me with those—those burning eyes! If I tell anyone, I'll be ripped apart for blasphemy! B-But I know what I saw, and it wasn't Tyreen! I—I saw... an angel!
Hail, Sun Smashers! I am Mouthpiece, voice of the Children of the Vault! The Twin Gods have graciously offered you an Eridium-tier membership in our family, in exchange for the Sacred Vault Map.

Our Eridium-tier members will enjoy VIP access when we open the Great Vault, along with a bottomless supply of meat and a special edition custom death car. I should stress that this is a limited-time offer.
Once we receive the map, our followers will escort you to the welcome ceremony. In preparation for our arrival, purge your clan of any free thinkers before entry. The Great Vault beckons!
Citizen: this planet is now property of the Maliwan Corporation. By remaining in the city, you've implicitly signed a non-compete agreement with Maliwan. This camp violates that agreement.
What are you talking about? They're just tents, we're not competing with anything. We're just trying to survive.
Maliwan has a robust catalog of emergency shelters available for purchase. Any off-brand shelters are considered competition and are to be destroyed immediately.
No, stop! You can't—
Pyrotech! All these ones right here. Hose 'em.
Ah, another day in the free market.
I'm Shanneth Kyrie and this is your Morning Meridian. We're here this morning with Rhys Strongfork, the CEO and re-founder of Atlas Corporation. Welcome, Rhys!
Great to be here, Shanneth.
Rhys, in bringing Atlas back into the galactic market, you've done something many would have thought impossible only a decade ago. What's the secret to your success?

Secret alien technology, Shanneth. Hahahaha! I'm—I'm kidding. Atlas is thriving because we've taken it in a new direction. I believe a company should lift its employees on its shoulders, not the other way around.
And what about your competition? Atlas has been attracting a lot of attention. Have you had any buyout offers?

I'll be honest, we've gotten some pretty, uh... aggressive offers from certain legacy weapons brands, but I'm not selling. Atlas is a stand-alone brand, and it's gonna stay that way. As long as I'm alive. Agh, why did I say that? Y-You can cut that, right? Right? It's live? Aghhh, Jerry, why're you always scheduling these things?

This is Captain Traunt's personal log. And if any of you statue polishers are listening to this, you're gonna get what's comin' to ya.||Ahem. Why do I always resort to taunts? 'Cause, when I was a little kid, everyone used to call me little Sammy Taunt, heh-heh. I'd scream, “My name is Samuel Traunt! With an 'r'!” But they'd never call me by my real name. Well, I got real good at taunting real quick, and it's been my most loyal weapon ever since.

Okay, the course is going great, but now they're saying I need specimens to do tests on. Where the heck am I gonna get brain samples from? Agh, crap, Rhys just sent me a maintenance order on a ratch nest in Sector 19. Ughh, I'll never save my friend if I keep having to clear out ratches! Unless...

All right, day thirty-two of neuro-transfer trials. Had a lot of misfires, but that's how you improve, right? Containment on the invalid specimens has proven... tricky, but that's the great thing about abandoned labs: there's always cages! As long as we don't lose power, they'll stay put. But this is a corporate headquarters, no way are we losing power!

Alistair! Where the hell are you, Alistair? Damn it, the lodge was the place, but you went to find her anyway, didn't you? You fool! You damn bastard!||We were supposed to meet at the lodge. My old man's dead, Alistair. Those Calypsos snuffed him out, and they're comin' for me! If you don't show, I'll burn the whole planet down, I swear!||My family lands are crawlin' with zealots, and all I've got left is a shotgun with my name on it, and a... surprisingly empty bottle of whiskey. No word from Clay. Figures. A smuggler's never around when trouble comes. It's up to me now. Gotta sober up. Gotta fight like hell. They killed him while he was butterin' a damn biscuit, those craven DEVILS!
I don't know. Maybe it'd be better if I weren't a Jakobs. I ain't cut to lead. I got small ambitions and I can barely hit a grog from the porch at midday. What kinda man am I?
A good one.

[sighs] Jakobs is a family corporation, Alistair. Passed down by blood. If I don't take it up, some long-lost cousin'll have the reins and muck the whole thing up. My father wants Jakobs to be about more than guns. It's about reliance. About civility. Honor.
Sounds to me as though you're just the man to carry the name.
Not so sure about that. But maybe if you stick around, I might pick up something.
All of my ambitions are right here with you, Winny.
And damn it, if that ain't why I love ya.

I'm drunk. And I know you're drunk too, and that's why you're gon' sit there and let me have my say! Here it is. My say. I ain't the one, Monty. I ain't the one. You're getting older, who knows how many years you got left, so you're thinkin' about your heir. Well, that Clay's the man for the job. He's the son you wanted all this time anyway! What a sight. A reformed smuggler leadin' Jakobs into the horizon. Me, I'm gon' live my life. I ain't much of a gunslinger, and to all those bastards out there, that means I ain't a Jakobs. But this ain't Alistair's doing, do you hear me? It's my say. About damn time I had it.
Your butler said you wanted to talk.
That's my boyfriend, and his name is Alistair.
He don't talk like us, does he?
No, he don't.

I wanted to talk about Jakobs.

Your daddy's fine. Monty's spooked, that's all. Galaxy's burnin' down, and he wants to know how far it'll spread. But none of the other corporations know what to do—join forces or grab a torch and hope the winds don't change. But Eden'll be fine—if there ain't no Vault, the Children won't come to play.
Yeah. Yeah, see that's what I want to discuss. Time's come to let you in on a family secret.
Well, I gotta be family for that, don't I?
Don't get ahead of yourself, slick.
Troy, these bandits are staring at me. Gross, that one's wearing skag testicles as a necklace. Or a snack. What am I supposed to say?
Here. Try this.

KILL THE SIREN WITCH!
BURN HER!

What the hell did she do to Jaw Breaker?
Flee in panic! Trample all in your path!
[wails]
That went well.

[screams]

Burn her!

But they're sharpening their teeth with rusty blades and wiping blood on their tongues.

[cheers]
Join me, my Eridium-blighted family! And together we will conquer Pandora and spread out planet by planet, until the entire universe is ours!
[cheers]

Fine.||So, you there. Yes, you with the dog's ear sewn to your mouth as a makeshift tongue. What do you want?

My dream? Yes—yes, my eyes drip salami juice. The moon has stolen my gut beans. Then, the Vault Hunter comes. With a hundred arms, firing, laughing! I try to flee, but my legs have traitored me—a betrayal of the ground! I am cheese, full of holes and stinking! I... I... gahhghgh!
Follow me, and you will never die! Never age! Never be hungry again! And the only tears you cry will be tears of sweet victory... as we head towards the Great Vault!
[cheers]
The Great Vault. Agh, that is some good shit, Ty. I can work with that.
It's time to teach my children a lesson, Troy.||Three bandits, now!||So—which of you, my sweet children, can tell me what five plus seven is? That's five plus seven. Five and seven.
Five. Seven! No... marmalade! Yeah, marmalade! MARMALADE!
Twelve!
And you? Do you know the answer?
No, Vault Mother. I can't count! I bite my nails when I get nervous! [sobbing] I bit off all my fingers! Don't sacrifice me! I beg you!
Are you done? Good! Twelve is the correct answer.
In my clan, marmalade means twelve! I swear it.
I have no fingers!
I was right! Did my answer please you, Vault Mother? Am I to be Anointed?||No... but—agghgh!
No—don't kill me! Aghhgahgah!
W-Why did you kill him? He spoke twelve! The righteous number!
First, that's not what righteous means. Don't use words you don't know. And second, I SACRIFICED him, remember? THAT'S the word we use when I take someone's life.
Why did you... sacrifice him, God-Queen?
I do not want answers from you, EVER. You will seek answers from me.||Now go SACRIFICE some Vault Thieves.

Oh, look! The entries from Troy's “Praise Be The God-Queen” poetry competition are in. Let's see...||This one's from a young psycho named Gut Rot.||“Roses are red, but Pandora has none. Tyreen is the Vault Girl. She is my sun.”||       ||Aw, that's so sweet! But he didn't get my title right, so... sacrifice him.
He's only seven, God-Queen! And he's got a gimp leg!
Oh! [winces] Oh, I didn't realize. Then, he'll be easier to catch, won't he?

Gaha! I brim with glorious purpose! Long have I sloshed emptily without aim, my walls reddened only by the hapless few. But the TWIN GODS have filled me with sanguine fervor! And now I roil and burble to think of the day when we overflow, spilling out until the whole sky is red!

Ragh! Rgh. The sand reddens as night falls. A new clan has arrived in the Droughts. Scorcheye says they have conquered every clan from the Parched Fathoms to Devil's Razor Ridge. Their leader is a witch! Scorcheye claims she can devour a man with her mind!

Feels like I been workin' on this ship forever and ever, huh? I sure hope the wait's been worth it. The Sanctuary III is like a big souped up version of Sanctuary with high-octane fuel pumping through her sexy caboose. It's more mobile than Sanctuary and prettier'n all get out. Scooter'd be proud, I think. We don't talk about Sanctuary II, though. Probably better that way.

Ever since that Hector sumbitch took down Sanctuary, we've been up to our tits in bandits. The Crimson Raiders sure as hell took a beatin' over the last few years. But with Lilith at the helm, I know we'll keep standin' strong. We've spent the last I-don't-know-how-long followin' one Vault Map lead after another, and we ain't turned up jack squat. But Lil said she's got a new lead and I got a feelin' we're gettin' closer.

Them COV keep comin' at the queen, and gettin' right smacked down for their trouble. I'm the queen, by the way. I ain't never needed no one protectin' me, that's for sure. I can hold my own, even on a planet savage as this one. But joinin' up with the Raiders was the best call I ever made. It's like family. And after Scooter died, I got family in short supply these days.
Amara, my favorite client! Great to see you, baby.
Don't call me baby. I'm the Tiger, remember?

Easy, easy, baby! Ghguhh! Okay, that—that was a mistake, tiger. THE Tiger! Put me down! Listen, I'm your agent. I'm lookin' out for you. And I'm telling ya, you've outgrown Partali. You beat down the gangs, lifted up the people, but there's no one left to fight. Legends gotta keep being written, you know? Be reborn! Or they die.
That's why I'm leaving. I've heard of a place Sirens are drawn to—and now I feel it, too. Pandora.
Pandora? Hoo. That's a rough place, ba—Tiger. Lots of fights there. Cannibal bandits, vicious wildlife, even alien stuff.
I know, right? It's perfect.
Five more missions and your contract's up! Then you're free to go!
You said that five missions ago.
No—I said five missions three missions ago, and three missions five missions ago. Get it straight, soldier! Besides, numbers don't matter. Wars matter. You wanna win this war or what?
“Or what” sounds good.

I don't give two turds in a Vercuvian ham sandwich what sounds good to you, soldier! You signed a contract. If you wanna keep that Iron Bear unit, it's five more missions. Besides, I need you out there with the greenies. You quit, they die.
Ugh, fine. ONE more mission. Where we goin'?
Darzaran Bay.
F***ing motherf***er piece of s***ing f***meat!
And... gotcha!
Ghahaha! Zane, hrk... wait!

Barnabus, ya old bastard! Come to assassinate me, did ya? Under whose contract? No, wait—let's make it a game! Hyperion? No? The Obsidian Block? Pangolin? Hephaestus United? Maliwan? Am I getting closer, Barny? Hot or cold?
Okay... all of them. Ghgh... and... Cutlord Karuu.
Cutlord Karuu? Shite! Been years since I did a job for her!
